    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratore</ex></expan> Caesare Divi <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilio</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usto</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pont</abbr><ex>ifice</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>max</abbr><ex>imo</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>tr</abbr><ex>ibunicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan> XXIV co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ule</ex></expan> XIII patre <expan><abbr>patr</abbr><ex>iae</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>Annobal Rufus ornator patriae amator concordiae <lb n="3"/>flamen sufes <expan><abbr>praef</abbr><ex>ectus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>sacr</abbr><ex>orum</ex></expan> Himilchonis Tapapi <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ua</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ecunia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>fac</abbr><ex>iendum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>coer</abbr><ex>avit</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>idemq</abbr><ex>ue</ex></expan> dedicavit
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Unterhalb des lateinischen Textes zwei Zeilen in neopunischer Sprache. Der Text findet sich in diesem Theater zwei weitere Male: am östlichen Orchestraausgang (IRT 322) und am östlichen Theatereingang (IRT 323). Lintel block; text carved within a tabula ansata.</p>
            </div>
